[2] India - Tilpura

Date: Thu, 26 Jan 2012
Source: Zeenews [edited]
http://zeenews.india.com/news/north-east/bird-flu-reappears-in-tripura_755010.html

Bird flu reappears in Tripura
-----------------------------
Bird flu has reappeared in Lembucherra area, about 45 km from here [Agartala], official sources said Thursday [26 Jan 2012].

Following reports of deaths of poultry birds in the area, blood samples were collected and examined and H5 strain of avian influenza virus was found, officials said.

More than 2000 ducks and birds would be culled tomorrow [Fri, 27 Jan 2012] in the area.

Meanwhile, the state administration has formed 16 rapid response teams to cull the ducks and birds in the area.

Sources said, BSF [Border Security Force] was alerted so that no poultry could enter into Indian territory. Tripura has 856-km-long border with Bangladesh.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[Tripura is a state in North-East India, with an area of 4051 sq mi (10 490 sq/km. It is the third smallest state of India, based on total area, surrounded by Bangladesh on the north, south, and west. The Indian states of Assam and Mizoram lie to the east. The statement "no poultry (from Tripura) could enter into Indian territory" could be read while keeping in mind that Tripura was formerly an independent kingdom, merged with independent India in 1949. For a map, see
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:India_Tripura_locator_map.svg. -Mod.AS].


