[4] Bhutan - poultry
Date: 25 Jan 2012
Source: Meat Trade News Daily [edited]
http://www.meattradenewsdaily.co.uk/news/250112/bhutan___bird_flu_strikes_again_.aspx

Bhutan - Bird flu strikes again
-------------------------------
87 cases of highly pathogenic avian influenza have been confirmed in Thimphu, Bhutan.

The cases occurred on a backyard poultry farm adjacent to the national highway.
1241 birds have been destroyed and any remaining susceptible poultry birds in the affected area will be culled.

